    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect HARQ retransmission due to bfly4_tw1 radix-4 butterfly computation error\n\n### Summary\nThe radix-4 butterfly function `bfly4_tw1` in the NEON-optimized DFT implementation was producing incorrect output values, causing HARQ processes to use wrong redundancy versions during retransmissions. This led to failed retransmissions and reduced throughput in downlink transmissions.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts_neon.c`: Fixed `bfly4_tw1` and `ibfly4_tw1` functions to compute correct radix-4 butterfly outputs\n- Corrected output ordering to match standard FFT implementation\n- Made implementation consistent with manual optimizations in dft16/idft16 functions\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a UE with HARQ enabled in downlink\n2. Trigger retransmissions by intentionally corrupting initial transmissions\n3. Observe that retransmitted TBs use incorrect redundancy versions\n4. Monitor for increased BLER and reduced throughput in poor channel conditions\n5. Check PHY logs for \"HARQ retransmission failed\" messages\n\nThe issue manifests as incorrect softbuffer combining at the UE side due to mismatched redundancy versions between initial transmission and retransmissions, causing decode failures even with sufficient SNR.\n"
}